Chairman, North Central Governors’ Forum (NCGF) Abubakar Sani Bello, on Tuesday, congratulated the sterling and exemplary leadership of Vice President of Nigeria, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo, having turned 65. This was contained in a statement on Tuesday by Mary Noel-Berje, Chief Press Secretary to the Governor of Niger State. According to the statement, Sani Bello, who is also Niger State governor, in his congratulatory birthday message, described Prof. Osinbajo, who turned 65 years, as “a detribalized and humble personality that believes in the corporate existence of the country.” He said, “the Vice president has contributed immensely to the growth and development of the country through his leadership qualities devoid of sentiments, hence the need for all Nigerians to celebrate, and honour him.” According to the statement, “the Vice President has proven to be a true Nigerian, pious, sincere and dedicated to his duties”, adding that “he is an exemplary leader worthy of emulation and should be commended and celebrated.” He prayed God to continue to guide and protect him, grant him good health and more wisdom to continue to deliver purposeful leadership to the country.